Its spokesman Bongani Nqulunga says there are 12 public holidays a year, and workers are entitled to them all. JOHANNESBURG The Presidency says Tuesday remains a public holiday because workers should not be inconvenienced because of an unusual occurrence of a Christmas on a Sunday.Its spokesman Bongani Nqulunga says there are 12 public holidays a year and workers are entitled to them all.President Jacob Zuma declared the day a holiday on the 19 September 2016.Nqulunga says a number of enquiries about the day were made, and they now seek to clarify it. The declaration of 27 December as a public holiday will ensure that workers are not unduly disadvantaged because of this unusual occurrence and they are still entitled to their 12 paid public holidays. 